        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 2:07PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 207 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong and slow moving
thunderstorm over Littleton, or 11 miles west of Roanoke Rapids.
This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Littleton, Weldon, Rosemary, Southpointe And
Morningstar Marinas, Roanoke Rapids Lake, and Lake Gaston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Very heavy rain can be expected due to the slow movement of this
storm. Prolonged heavy rain will result in ponding of water on
roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and minor flooding of
creeks and streams. Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra
caution to avoid hydroplaning.</instruction>
